'''Paolo Giancarlo Faletti Ghislimberti''' (19 May 1967 - 10 September 2000) was an Italian volunteer firefighter and youth coach. He was killed by a loose wheel from the Jordan of [[Heinz-Harald Frentzen]]'s Jordan Formula One car in the [[2000 Italian Grand Prix]].

==Biography==
Ghislimberti was born in Trento, Italy and often spent his spare time working as Deputy Commander of the volunteer firefighter brigade in [[Lavis]] where he lived. In 1990, he was a member of the CEA Squadra Corse, a well known firefighter company that fielded more than 200 men. Ghislimberti also worked as a youth coach for the [[Trentino Volley]] team.<ref name=memorial>{{cite web|title=Paolo Ghislimberti|url=http://www.motorsportmemorial.org/focus.php?db=ct&n=284|publisher=Motorsport Memorial|accessdate=29 July 2012}}</ref>

===Death===
In the 2000 Italian Grand Prix, Ghislimberti was working for CEA Squadra Corse at Monza. Before the start of the race, he moved further up from his post taking his fire extingusher with him. During the first lap of the race, Ghislimberti had stopped for a brief moment after running back to check on his fire-fighting equipment as a multiple-car accident at the Variante della Roggia corner saw a wheel from [[Heinz-Harald Frentzen]]'s Jordan struck Ghislimberti with full force leading to massive head and chest injuries.<ref>{{cite web|last=Tremayne|first=David|title=Safety in F1 - an ever-moving target|url=http://www.grandprix.com/ft/ftdt002.html|publisher=grandprix.com|date=2000-09-12}}</ref> He red helmet came loose and rolled near towards the side of the track. Another standing next to Ghislimberti attempted to save his life before medical help from [[Sid Watkins]] and [[Gary Hartstein]] arrived on the scene. He was taken to the First Aid Room at Monza Hospital where he was pronounced dead.<ref>{{cite web|last=Nidetz|first=Stephen|title=Offical Killed In Italian Race|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2000-09-11/sports/0009110186_1_rubens-barrichello-monza-circuit-michael-schumacher|publisher=Chicago Tribune|date=2000-09-11}}</ref> Ghisliberti's death was the first [[Formula One]] related fatility since the death of [[Ayrton Senna]] in the [[1994 San Marino Grand Prix]] and the first for a by-stander since Team Osella mechanic Giovanni Amadeo was killed in the pitlane at [[Zolder]] in May 1981. An autopsy reported that Ghislimberti also suffered from cardiac arrest when the wheel of Frentzen's car struck the marshal.<ref>{{cite web|title=Formula 1 News - September 2000|url=http://www.fedef1.com/news/f1n_sep00.html|publisher=F1 News|accessdate=29 July 2012}}</ref> He was survived by his pregnant wife of two years Elena who had a daughter named Lisa born in December 2000 and has received finanical help from the Formula One community via a fund.<ref name=memorial /> His parents. two brothers and sister also outlived him.<ref>{{cite web|title=Carambola cursed, Death of a volunteer|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/2000/settembre/11/Carambola_maledetta_muore_volontario_co_0_00091110446.shtml|publisher=Corriere Della Sera|date=2000-09-11}}</ref> [[Bernie Ecclestone]] donated $40,000 and the teams donated $10,000 with the drivers holding an auction to sell their overalls used in the [[2000 United States Grand Prix]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Motorsport People - G|url=http://www.teamdan.com/people/g.html#Paolo%20Ghislimberti .|publisher=GEL Motorsport|accessdate=29 July 2012}}</ref>

===Funeral===
Ghislimberti's Funeral was held in Lavis at the San Ulderico church on 14 September. His coffin was wrapped with flag of [[Ferrari]] as Ghislimberti had a passion for the team was respented by [[Luca Badoer]], Claudio Berro and [[Stefano Domenicali]]. A cusion of pink flowers and headphones were accompanied by fellow firefighters. 110 red roses were sent by [[Rubens Barrichello]] and Heinz-Harald Frentzen and [[Gaston Mazzacane]] was present along with his widow Elena and other friends and relatives. Wreaths from the top teams and the [[FIA]] were sent for the occasion.<ref>{{cite web|title=A Last Tribute to Paolo Ghislimberti|url=http://www.rds.ca/f1/chroniques/116708.html|publisher=RDS.ca|date=2000-09-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Jordan drivers attend Ghislimberti's funeral|url=http://www.grandprix.com/ns/ns02828.html|publisher=grandprix.com|date=2000-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Formula One says good-bye to Paolo|url=http://www.gpupdate.net/en/f1-news/11818/formula-one-says-good-bye-to-paulo/|publisher=gpupdate.net|date=2000-09-15}}</ref>

